This example illustrates how an outlier can affect the mean.  The mean with the outlier was 27.9 and the corrected mean is 23.3.

  
\subsubsection{Median}

The \emph{median} is the value that is less affected by an outlier than the mean.  It is the middle observation of the sorted dataset.  After we arrange the ages (from low to high) of the students from STAT 2830 class, we find the middle value.  Let's use the original dataset with the outlier; See Table 3.1.  Let's make the following observations:

\begin{itemize}
\item If there is an odd number of data values in our dataset, we must arrange the values in increasing magnitude (from the smallest to the largest) and locate the center value, e.g., 

