\end{table}


\item median = 24

\item Suppose that we found another student who was nineteen years old and added her to the dataset of students, we can ask how does this additional student affect the median.  In other words, if there is an even number of data values in our dataset, we must order the values at the beginning and end and locate the two center value and average them, e.g., 

